Toy Example

#' @title area of rectangle
#' @description calculates the area of a rectangle
#' @param len length of the rectangle (numeric)
#' @return computed area

rect_area <- function(len = 1, wid = 1){
  if(len < 0) {
    stop("len must be positive")
  }
  if (wid < 0) {
    stop("wild must be positive")
  }
  area <- len * wid
  return(area)
}
Testing rect_area
rect_area()
## [1] 1
rect_area(len = 2, wid = 3)
## [1] 6

composite functions

#' @title composite function f(gx)
#' @description runs the g(x) function within f(x)
#' @param x number
#' @return number

fog <- function(x){
  fg <- f(g(x))
  return(fg)
}

fog(2)
## [1] 81
fog(-5)
## [1] 25
#' @title composite function g(f(x))
#' @description runs the f(x) function within g(x)
#' @param x number
#' @return number

gof <- function(x){
  gf <- g(f(x))
  return(gf)
}

gof(0)
## [1] 5
gof(-5/2)
## [1] 17.5

Pythagoras

#' @title Pythagoras formula
#' @description used to compute the length of a hypotenuse of a right triangle with legs of length (a) and length (b)
#' @param a 
#' @param b
#' @return number

pythagoras <- function(a,b){
  p <- sqrt(((a^2) + (b^2)))
  return (p)
}

pythagoras(3,4)
## [1] 5
#' @title modified Pythagoras formula
#' @description used to compute the length of a hypotenuse of right triangle
#' @param a
#' @param b
#' @return number

pythagoras <- function(a, b = a){
  p <- sqrt(((a^2) + (b^2)))
  return (p)
}

pythagoras(5)
## [1] 7.071068

Area of a circle

#' @title Area of Circle
#' @description computes area of a circle
#' @param radius
#' @return area

circle_area <- function(radius = 1){
  c <- pi * radius^2
  return (c)
}

circle_area()
## [1] 3.141593
circle_area(radius = 3)
## [1] 28.27433
#' @title Modified Area of Circle
#' @description computes area of a circle with positive numbers
#' @param radius
#' @return area

circle_area <- function(radius = 1){
    if(radius < 0) {
    stop("radius cannot be negative")
  }
  d <- pi * radius^2
  return(d)
}

circle_area(radius = -2)
## Error in circle_area(radius = -2): radius cannot be negative

Surface of a Cylinder

#' @title Cylinder Area
#' @description computes area of cylinder
#' @param radius
#' @param height
#' @return number

cylinder_area <- function(radius = 1, height = 1){
  if(radius < 0) {
    stop("radius cannot be negative")
  }
  if (height < 0) {
    stop("height cannot be negative")
  }
  cy <- 2*circle_area(radius) + (2*pi*radius*height)
  return(cy)
  }

cylinder_area()
## [1] 12.56637
cylinder_area(radius = 2, height = 3)
## [1] 62.83185

Volume of a cylinder

#' @title Cylinder Volume
#' @description computes volume of cylinder
#' @param radius
#' @param height
#' @return number

cylinder_volume <- function(radius = 1, height = 1){
  v <- circle_area(radius) * height
  return(v)
}

cylinder_volume(radius = 3, height = 10)
## [1] 282.7433
cylinder_volume(height = 10, radius = 3)
## [1] 282.7433

gallons to liters, and vice versa
#' @title Gallons to Liters
#' @description converts gallons to liters
#' @param x
#' @return number

gallons2liters <- function(x){
  g <- x * 3.78541
  return(g)
}

#' @title Liters to gallons
#' @description converts liters to gallons
#' @param x
#' @return number

liters2gallons <- function(x){
  l <- x / 3.78541
  return (l)
}

Polynomials

poly1 <- function(x) {
  x^3
}
x <- seq(-4,4, length.out = 20)
y <- poly1(x)

plot(x,y, type = 'l', lwd = 4, col = '#0000FF', las = 1)
abline(h = 0, v = 0, col = '#000000', lwd = 1)
title(main = expression(paste(f(x), '=', x^3)))

poly2 <- function(x) {
  (x^2 - 1)*((x+3)^3)
}
x <- seq(-4,4, length.out = 20)
y <- poly2(x)

plot(x,y, type = 'l', lwd = 4, col = '#0000FF', las = 1)
abline(h = 0, v = 0, col = '#000000', lwd = 1)
title(main = expression(paste(f(x), '=', (x^2 -1)*((x+3)^3))))

poly3 <- function(x) {
  ((x^2 -1)*(x^2-9))
}

Multiple If’s
#' @title Even
#' @description informs you if a number is even or not
#' @param x
#' @return number
is_even <- function(x){
  if(x %% 2 == 0) {
    return(TRUE)
  }else{
    return(FALSE)
  }
}

is_even(10)
## [1] TRUE
is_even(33)
## [1] FALSE
#' @title Odd
#' @description informs you if a number is odd or not
#' @param x
#' @return number
is_odd <- function(x) {
  if(is_even(x) == TRUE) {
    return(FALSE)
  } else{
    return(TRUE)
  }
}

is_odd(1)
## [1] TRUE
is_odd(4)
## [1] FALSE

Grading Function

#' @title Grade
#' @description shows the grade received for scores between 0 and 100
#' @param score
#' @return character
grade <- function(score){
  if(score >= 90 & score <= 100){
    return ("A")
  }
  if (score >= 80 & score < 90){
    return("B")
  }
  if (score >= 70 & score < 80){
    return("C")
  }
  if (score >= 60 & score < 70){
    return("D")
  }
  if (score < 60) {
    return("F")
  }
  if (score < 0 | score > 100){
   stop("score must be a number between 0 and 100") 
  }
  return(grade)
}

grade(score = 90)
## [1] "A"
grade(score = 89.9999)
## [1] "B"
grade(score = 70.0000001)
## [1] "C"
grade(score = 50)
## [1] "F"

Converting miles to other units
#' @title miles to inches
#' @description converts miles to inches
#' @param x
#' @return number

miles2inches <- function(x){
 i <-  x * 63360
 return(i)
}

#' @title miles to feet
#' @description converts miles to feet
#' @param x
#' @return number

miles2feet <- function(x){
  f <- x * 5280
  return(f)
}

#' @title miles to yards
#' @description converts miles to yards
#' @param x
#' @return number

miles2yards <- function(x) {
  y <- x*1760
  return(y)
}

#' @title miles to meters
#' @description converts miles to meters
#' @param x
#' @return number 
  
miles2meters <- function(x){
  m <- x/0.00062137
  return(m)
}

#' @title miles to kilometers
#' @description converts miles to kilometers
#' @param x
#' @return number

miles2kms <- function(x){
  k <- x/0.62137
  return(k)
}

Using switch()
convert <- function(x, to = 'km') {
  switch(to, 'km' = miles2kms(x), 'in'= miles2inches(x), 'ft' = miles2feet(x), 'yd' = miles2yards(x), 'm' = miles2meters(x))
}

convert(3, 'in')
## [1] 190080
convert(3, 'ft')
## [1] 15840
convert(3, 'yd')
## [1] 5280
convert(3, 'm')
## [1] 4828.041
convert(3, 'km')
## [1] 4.828041
